iv_add_cmod","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Int/Linear.lean#L244-L250"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Linear.html#Int.Internal.Linear.cmod\"><span class=\"name\">Int</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linear</span>.<span class=\"name\">cmod</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the ceiling-compatible remainder of the division `a / b`.\nThis function ensures that the remainder is consistent with `cdiv`, meaning:\n```\na = b * cdiv a b + cmod a b\n```\nSee theorem `cdiv_add_cmod`. We also have\n```\n-b < cmod a b ≤ 0\n```\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Int/Linear.html#Int.Internal.Linear.cmod","kind":"def","line":229,"name":"Int.Internal.Linear.cmod","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Int/Linear.lean#L229-L242"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Linear.html#Int.Internal.Linear.cdiv\"><span class=\"name\">Int</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linear</span>.<span class=\"name\">cdiv</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the ceiling of the division `a / b`. That is, the result is equivalent to `⌈a / b⌉`.\nExamples:\n- `cdiv 7 3` returns `3`\n- `cdiv (-7) 3` returns `-2`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Int/Linear.html#Int.Internal.Linear.cdiv","kind":"def","line":219,"name":"Int.Internal.Linear.cdiv","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Int/Linear.lean#L219-L227"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Linear.html#Int.Internal.Linear.Expr.norm\"><span class=\"name\">Int</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linear</span>.<span class=\"name\">Expr</span>.<span class=\"name\">norm</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Linear.html#Int.Internal.Linear.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Linear.html#Int.Internal.Linear.Poly\">Poly</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Converts the given expression into a polynomial, and then normalizes it. ","docLink":"./Init/Data/Int/Linear.html#Int.Internal.Linear.Expr.norm","kind":"def","line":214,"name":"Int.Internal.Linear.Expr.norm","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Int/Linear.lean#L214-L217"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Linear.html#Int.Internal.Linear.Expr.toPoly'.go\"><span class=\"name\">Int</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linear</span>.<span class=\"name\">Expr</span>.<span class=\"name\">toPoly'</span>.<span class=\"name\">go</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">coeff</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</sp